(253729, 8448, 253715, 'Ahnab', 6111, '', 1331300904, 'Here''s the major difference between JHP''s & FMJ''s:-\n\n[B]JHP''s:-[/B]\n1) Have a lower penetration than an FMJ''s\n2) Mushroom upon impact and slow down almost immediately (due to the sudden drag created by the mushroom head), whereby they transfer total kinetic energy more efficiently and quickly\n3) The mushroom has the added bonus of creating a much bigger entry wound and channel\n4) Due to the mushrooming effect and immediate loss of kinetic energy, a JHP will rarely over-penetrate the target, and will instead tumble inside the target (whereby causing much more internal damage)\n5) As such, a JHP is ideally suited against "soft targets" (e.g. humans, etc.)\n\n[B]FMJ''s:-[/B]\n1) Have higher & greater penetration than JHP''s\n2) Have a relatively poor kinetic energy transfer upon impact, because of which an FMJ will retain a large degree of forward momentum and will usually over-penetrate the target\n3) The entry wound and channel is considerably smaller than that of n JHP\n4) As such, an FMJ is best suited against "hard targets" (walls, doors, etc.)\n\nHope I covered everything and made sense! :)', 1, 1, '175.110.150.75', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
