(255973, 8492, 255427, 'pg7', 6804, '', 1332169289, '[QUOTE=pg7;255427]On my baikal SxS barrel, 65MPa (9700PSI) pressure is engraved which is less than Saami Spec for 12guage shot gun of 11500psi. Gun was purchased in 1996. Now if cartridges are being manufactured according to Saami Specs, is it safe to shoot them thru these barrels or my understanding of whole issue is wrong?[/QUOTE]\nFinally i was able to get answer of my above query. Actually, barrel has been hydraucally tested at 65MPa. This means that barrel weakest part ie muzzle end can hold this pressure. This implies that the chamber area can bear pressure much greater than this value as wall thickness is three times the muzzle end wall thickness. Peak pressure happens in the chamber area after 0.5millisecond of triggering while the load exits muzzle after 1.5 millisecond. Upto this time the peak pressure of the order of 9000~8000psi lowers upto 1000psi. So my gun pressure rating is more than safe.', 1, 0, '182.177.222.41', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
