(257403, 8148, 243588, 'kf7mjf', 6942, '', 1332782722, 'Ah I see they are importing a "neutered" version of it. No folding stock, no accessory rails, no muzzle device... To answer an earlier question, the US has stupid import laws.  "Assault" weapons cannot be readily imported. Instead you have to bring them in without some of the cool features, and then rebuild them in the US with a certain number of US made parts.  For example, one type of Kalashnikov that is widely sold in the US comes in only able to take 10 round magazines, and then is opened up to take hi capacity mags, and rebuilt with enough US made parts to no longer be considered "imported".  It is something designed just to make it harder to import cool (that is to say) "scary" guns.  Pure madness. So when I see a stock VEPR 12 with all the cool stuff on it, readily imported elsewhere it makes me sad and angry.', 1, 0, '208.54.32.179', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
